Class CustomHashmap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.CustomHashmap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of key
    V - type of value

    public class CustomHashmap<K,V>
extends Object
    A custom hashmap that can take different key and value types. Uses an internal static class for entries.
    Author:
    jussiste

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put(K key,
                V value)
        Method to insert an entry to the hashmap. If there is already an entry at the place the hash points to, this method checks if it has the same key. If the key is the same this method will override the value, if it is not the same the method will find a new place for the entry.
        Parameters:
        key - key value
        value - value

      • get

        public V get(K key)
        A method to fetch an value out of the hashmap using a key.

        Returns:
        value

        public boolean remove(K key)
        Method that removes a given key from the hashmap along with it's value.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if the removal was succesfull, false otherwise.
